about: Dr. Aniss Moumen is a Professor of Computer Science at the National School of Applied Sciences (ENSA), Ibn Tofail University, Kenitra, Morocco. He holds a Ph.D. in Computer Science, Mathematics, and Applications (2016) from Ibn Tofail University. He also earned a specialized master‚Äôs in Information Security and Systems (2005) from the Higher School of Computer Science, Electronics, and Automation (ESIEA) in Paris, a master‚Äôs in Networks and Telecommunications (2004) from Chouaib Doukkali University, and a Bachelor of Engineering in Computer Science, Electronics, Electrotechnics, and Automation (2002) from Sidi Mohammed Ben Abdellah University. Before becoming a professor, Dr. Moumen spent 13 years working as a network administrator and senior developer for several national and international companies, including Logica, AXA, CGI, ATOS, Capgemini, Mundiapolis, and STCR. This industry experience provided him with practical expertise in network management, software development, and information systems, which he now integrates into his academic work. At ENSA Kenitra, he teaches programming (Java, Python), Compilation and Language theory, data analysis and data mining (R, Python), databases, geographic information systems (GIS), and web mapping. Dr. Moumen‚Äôs research focuses on artificial intelligence (AI) for societal impact, social computing, and educational technology. He explores how AI can address social challenges, improve public administration, and enhance service delivery. He is committed to supporting PhD students and researchers by organizing workshops on research methodology, quantitative data analysis using SPSS Statistics, SPSS AMOS, SmartPLS, and SPSS Modeler, and qualitative data analysis using NVIVO and IRAMUTEQ. He also delivers open workshops on scientific writing, research communication, and publication, helping young researchers develop essential academic skills. Dr. Moumen is the Editor-in-Chief of the Moroccan Journal of Quantitative and Qualitative Research (MJQR) and has edited two Springer books: "GIS, Applied Computing and Data Science for Water Management" and "Artificial Intelligence and Data Analytics for Innovative Applications in Engineering, Sustainability, and Technology." He regularly contributes to the international scientific community, serving as a peer reviewer for leading journals and co-chairing conferences in Tunisia, France, Turkey, and Morocco. His publications, indexed in Scopus and Web of Science, highlight the transformative role of AI and data science in education and public service.

built UI in Figma + React.js for field deployment.'}, {'name': '', 'description': None}, {'name': '', 'description': None}, {'name': '', 'description': None}, {'name': 'Real-Time Social Media and News Analysis with Machine Learning and Topic Modeling Algorithms', 'description': '- Developed a real-time data extraction and analysis pipeline using Apache Kafka to process social media posts and news articles. - Applied VADER, logistic regression, Latent Dirichlet Allocation (LDA), and K-means clustering for sentiment analysis, tokenization, topic modeling, and content categorization. - Designed interactive dashboards in Plotly Dash to visualize sentiment trends, thematic patterns, and clustered topic insights over time.Technologies: Python, Apache Kafka, Plotly Dash, VADER, SMOTE, TF-IDF vectorization, Logistic Regression, LDA, K-means Clustering'}, {'name': '', 'description': None}, {'name': '', 'description': None}, {'name': 'TrackHealth Pro: IoT and Secure Healthcare', 'description': '- Designed a secure IoT healthcare platform using AWS IoT Core, Apache Kafka, Docker, and TLS/SSL Encryption, ensuring compliance with ISO 27001. - Conducted risk assessments and proposed a security policy for data storage, sharing, and patient data management. - Developed a secure architecture diagram and implemented real-time monitoring and access control features.Technologies: AWS IoT Core, Apache Kafka, Docker, TLS/SSL Encryption, ISO 27001 Standards, AWS S3, Amazon Athena, IAM, OAuth, RBAC'}, {'name': '', 'description': None}, {'name': 'AI-Driven Equity in Moroccan Education : LLM-Powered policy recommendations', 'description': 'Key Features: - A dynamic dashboard for visualizing education data across regions. - Advanced analysis of performance metrics to highlight strengths and identify areas for improvement. - Tailored recommendations aligned with global OECD benchmarks. about: My journey as an engineer began with a five-year study in Electrical Engineering, where I explored everything from microcontrollers to power systems. While I started with low-level languages like Assembly, I fell in love with coding when I discovered I could use Java to build Android apps. That was the moment I realized my passion was not only for engineering, but also for creating practical tools that solve real problems. This led me to specialize in AI and Data Science at ENSAM in Meknes, where I combined my technical foundation with machine learning and software development skills. During my final-year internship in Strasbourg, I worked on an energy prediction project that used solar data and machine learning, and the resulting paper earned the First Best Paper Award at ICRERA 2024. A pivotal moment in my journey was discovering Linux and the open source world. It inspired me to give back by sharing knowledge, which is how my YouTube channel, 3CodeCamp, was born. This passion also led me to collaborate with freeCodeCamp, where I created courses on Elasticsearch, training LLMs from scratch, and the evolution of the Transformer architecture. Outside of my professional work, I am a passionate astronomer and astrophotographer, a hobby that began by chance and has grown to include my own telescope. This love for the cosmos is what inspired my main personal project, https://myuniversehub.com/. It is a full stack web app built with my favorite tools, Vue.js and Python. I am always looking for new ways to connect my passion for technology with my love for the universe.
projects: [{'name': 'The evolution of the Transformer architecture', 'description': 'Authored and produced a comprehensive course comparing the original 2017 Transformer architecture to its 2025 evolution. To empirically demonstrate the advancements, I built and benchmarked two separate models. The results showed that modern techniques like Rotary Positional Encoding (RoPE), Multi-head Latent Attention (MLA) significantly outperform the original architecture.'}, {'name': 'My Universe Hub: A Full-Stack APOD Redesign', 'description': "Motivated by a passion for astronomy, I developed MyUniverseHub to provide a modern, feature-rich, and more engaging user experience for NASA's Astronomy Picture of the Day (APOD) website. The full-stack application was built with a Django back end and a dynamic Vue.js front end, and is hosted on Digital Ocean.Key features include a robust search function, a trending page to rank images by likes, and a Favorites system for registered users. The content is kept up-to-date by an automated web scraper, built with BeautifulSoup, that extracts the latest images and data directly from NASA's official site."}, {'name': 'Elasticsearch Course for Beginners', 'description': 'Authored and published a comprehensive course on Elasticsearch for the freeCodeCamp channel. The curriculum covers fundamental concepts such as creating indices, managing documents, and using the Search API with Query DSL.To provide a complete learning path, the course also dives into advanced topics including data aggregations, ingest pipelines for pre-processing, KNN for semantic search, and managing time-series data.To bring all these concepts together, the course concludes with a hands-on project where learners build a full-stack astronomy application with a Vue.js front end and a FastAPI back end, all powered by Elasticsearch.'}, {'name': 'Course - Training a custom language model on personal chat data', 'description': "Produced a course demonstrating the end-to-end process of training a custom Large Language Model. projects: [{'name': 'AMDA - Advancing Multimodal Data Annotation for human-centric situations', 'description': 'Recent strides in AI research, particularly in computer vision and natural language processing, have significantly advanced the partial automation of data labeling and annotation processes. However, there remains a notable void in applying these cutting-edge techniques to videos portraying human-centric scenarios, with scant exploration of automated solutions for multimedia data. Current research primarily focuses on visual cues, such as on-screen detections, textual cues such as named entity recognition, and auditory cues involved in speech-to-text conversion. This project proposes a methodology that leverages state-of-the-art deep learning techniques to extract multimedia cues from videos.'}, {'name': 'Anime characters detector with TFrecords', 'description': 'Goal : Create a custom object detector for One Piece characters, trained on my own dataset (images and annotations), using a fine-tuned single-shot detector. about: I'm a seasoned Senior Machine Learning Engineer and Data Scientist with a Ph.D. in Computer Science, specializing in AI and NLP. projects: [{'name': 'AI-Powered Solution for Mental Health Disorder Detection and Therapeutic Assistance', 'description': 'This project involved the development of an advanced AI solution aimed at enhancing mental health support by utilizing a robust technology stack and innovative methodologies. The solution integrates various data sources to identify potential signs of mental health disorders and provide real-time assistance.Key Contributions:Machine Learning Models: Utilized Python with TensorFlow and PyTorch to train supervised learning models on datasets from Kaggle and other sources, achieving accurate detection of behaviors and emotional states indicative of mental health conditions.Therapeutic Chatbot: Developed a Flask-based chatbot employing prompt engineering to engage users in supportive conversations, offering personalized emotional support and coping strategies.Facial Expression Analysis: Applied OpenCV for image processing to detect subtle facial cues, enhancing the depth of emotional assessments.Real-Time Voice Emotion Recognition: Integrated real-time speech emotion recognition into a Streamlit interface, allowing immediate analysis of vocal inputs to detect emotional states.Interdisciplinary Research: Conducted extensive research in psychology and medicine to ground the solution in established theories and practices, ensuring relevance and effectiveness in mental health support.'}, {'name': '', 'description': None}, {'name': 'Driving Behavior Classification ‚Äì Multimodal Pipeline', 'description': 'This project focuses on the development of a multimodal machine learning and deep learning pipeline to predict and classify driving behavior . The classification relies on time-series data collected from accelerometer and gyroscope sensors, which capture the physical dynamics of vehicle movement.The modeling phase involved both traditional machine learning and advanced deep learning approaches. For the machine learning part, several classifiers were implemented and evaluated, including DecisionTreeClassifier, KNeighborsClassifier, and RandomForestClassifier. These models were trained on extracted and scaled features, and their performance was measured using standard metrics such as accuracy, precision, and recall. In parallel, a deep learning model was developed based on a Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) architecture, enhanced with Residual Blocks to facilitate deeper learning and Self-Attention mechanisms to better capture the most relevant temporal patterns in the sensor data. The deep learning model was trained using cross-validation techniques and optimized with early stopping to prevent overfitting. Final predictions were generated on unseen test data to assess the model‚Äôs generalization capability and real-world applicability.'}]

projects: [{'name': 'Analyzing Employee Satisfaction and "Big 5" Personality Characteristics change during Corona Virus', 'description': 'The analysis for this project was in the scoop of a sociology research focusing on employee satisfaction, the "Big 5" personality characteristics, how these elements intersect, and also how employee satisfaction has changed before and after the onset of the COVID-19 pandemic. Here are some key findings:ü§ù Employee Satisfaction Statistics:- Overall Employee Job Satisfaction (Oct 2020 and Sept 2022): Our analysis showed an increase in overall job satisfaction from October 2020 to September 2022, reflecting a shift in employee sentiments over this period.- Satisfaction Types (Culture & Environment, Management, Actual Job): Similar to overall satisfaction, satisfaction with culture and environment, management, and actual job displayed an overall increase during the same time frame.‚úÖ Correlation Analysis for "Big 5" Personality Measures:We explored relationships between the "Big 5" personality characteristics using the Spearman correlation coefficient. The analysis showed no significant strong correlations among these variables, providing valuable insights into how personality traits manifest in the workplace.‚úÖ Correlation Analysis for the Difference in Satisfaction (2022-2020):We analyzed the change in satisfaction between October 2020 and September 2022, considering the "Big 5" personality characteristics as predictors. The results revealed the role of Extraversion in predicting overall satisfaction change and provided a nuanced understanding of how personality traits influence satisfaction dynamics.üìà Decision Tree Model for Overall Job Satisfaction Difference:To offer a visual perspective on the relationship between "Big 5" personality traits and overall job satisfaction change, we employed a decision tree model. This tree revealed clear decision rules for predicting satisfaction changes based on Extraversion and Openness, underscoring the practicality of visual models in understanding complex data relationships.'}, {'name': 'Facebook Ads Analysis Dashboard', 'description': "As a small business looking to enhance your Facebook advertising strategy and drive better results, you need a powerful interactive dashboard that's tailor-made to help businesses like yours optimize their Facebook ad campaigns. üéØThe following dashboard was created in order to examine ad performance and decide what ad creatives to scale and what to improve, and provides the following solutions:1Ô∏è‚É£ Flexible Filters: Three handy filters for date range, campaign ID, and ad ID. This means you can easily customize your analysis based on your specific needs, ensuring every insight is relevant to your campaigns.2Ô∏è‚É£ Key Performance Indicators (KPIs): Keep an eye on crucial metrics with at-a-glance KPIs, including impressions, conversions, clicks, spending, and cost per click. These metrics are the heartbeat of your campaign's performance.3Ô∏è‚É£ Demographic Insights: Two captivating donut charts break down total conversions by age group and gender, giving you a deeper understanding of your audience. It's all about knowing who engages with your ads the most.4Ô∏è‚É£ Time Analysis: Our combo chart displays total clicks by the day of the week and the corresponding spending. Understand the best days to allocate your budget and drive more engagement.5Ô∏è‚É£ Trend Analysis: A sleek line chart shows the spending and clicks over the months. Spot trends and seasonality in your campaigns to fine-tune your strategy.6Ô∏è‚É£ Detailed Campaign Insights: The dashboard includes a comprehensive table with campaign and ad-specific data. Keep a close watch on campaign spending, impressions, clicks, conversions, and cost per click. This is where the nitty-gritty details come to life!Ready to supercharge your Facebook advertising efforts? I'm here to help! Let's collaborate to create a customized dashboard that aligns with your unique requirements and delivers actionable insights. ü§ù"}, {'name': 'Impact of electronic word of mouth on purchase intentions in the restaurant sector using the Snapchat platform', 'description': "An in-depth study on the influence of electronic word of mouth (EWOM) through the Snapchat platform on restaurant purchase intentions was conducted as a part of an academic research project.The primary goal was to examine the data collected through a survey of Saudi Arabian participants and construct statistical models to answer the research questions while exploring the conceptual framework.üîç The 4 research questions are:H1: Positive EWOM has a significant impact on purchasing intention.H2: Positive EWOM will positively influence higher EWOM intention on SNSs.H3: The greater the strength of the tie between the sender and the receiver, the greater the influence ofthe sender‚Äôs positive EWOM on the receiver‚Äôs purchase intention.H4: The stronger the link between the sender and receiver, that‚Äôs leads to higher the giving-EWOMintention on SNSs.‚úÖ Key Insights:Participants aged 25-34 represented the majority (43.75%).The survey predominantly attracted female participants (73.75%).Most participants held master's degrees or doctorates (66.25%).36.25% visited restaurants 2-3 times monthly.Snapchat was the top social media platform visited by participants (53.75%).‚úÖ Inferential Statistics:We utilized Structural Equation Modeling (SEM) to examine our hypotheses, focusing on the impact of positive EWOM on purchase intentions.Findings:- Positive EWOM significantly influenced purchase and giving intentions.- An increase of 1 in the positive EWOM scale led to a 1.117 increase in the purchase intentions scale and a 0.641 increase in the giving intentions scale."}, {'name': 'Monitoring Website Performance with the Bounce Rate Dashboard', 'description': "The motivation behind creating this dashboard was a critical concern - a high bounce rate on the client's website. A high bounce rate can signal a disconnect between what visitors expect and what the website delivers. Our aim was to closely monitor this rate, identify the types of devices and browsers contributing most to the bounce rate, and implement fixes to improve the user experience. But that's not all; we also wanted to track the effectiveness of these fixes over time.üí° The Solution: Bounce Rate DashboardOur Bounce Rate Dashboard was the answer the client needed to understand and address bounce rate challenges. Here's a glimpse of what it offers:‚úÖ Date Range Filter: With the ability to select specific date ranges, you can focus on a period of interest and assess the impact of changes over time.‚úÖ Key Performance Indicators (KPIs):Total Sessions, Total Visitors, Average Daily Session, Average Daily Visitors, Average Bounce Rate.‚úÖ Device and Browser Insights:Total Sessions by Device and Total Sessions by Browser: The two bar charts allow us to see which devices and browsers are most frequently used by visitors.‚úÖ Bounce Rate Trends:Average Bounce Rate vs. Total Sessions.Average Bounce Rate by Device.Average Bounce Rate by Browser.üíº Benefits of the Bounce Rate Dashboard- Improved User Experience: By identifying the devices and browsers causing high bounce rates.- Data-Driven Decision-Making: With real-time data at your fingertips, you can make informed decisions to enhance user engagement.- Fix Validation: Test your fixes and measure their effectiveness in reducing bounce rates.- Responsive Design: Optimize your website for specific devices or browsers based on insights.- Visitor Insights: Understand your audience's preferences and cater to their needs effectively.Connect with me to explore how this powerful tool can help reduce your bounce rate and improve your website's performance."}, {'name': 'Perception of the privacy and security of the Internet of Things (IoT) devices', 'description': "This project involved a comprehensive quantitative analysis of perceptions regarding the privacy and security of Internet of Things (IoT) devices. The study collected data from participants in Saudi Arabia and the United Kingdom, assessing their views on privacy, data security, and their knowledge about smart home devices.üí° Some Key Findings:- Demographics: The study included 130 participants (57%) from Saudi Arabia and 98 participants (43%) from the United Kingdom.- Education: Most participants in both countries held bachelor's degrees (40% for Saudi Arabia and 38.8% for the UK)- Privacy Concerns: 89.2% of participants in Saudi Arabia were concerned about the privacy and safety of their personal information, while 60.2% of UK participants shared the same concern.- Data Privacy Laws: Participants in the UK felt more protected by data privacy laws (66.3%) compared to those in Saudi Arabia (55.4%).- Knowledge About Smart Home Devices: Most participants from both countries reported having average knowledge about smart home devices (43.1% for Saudi Arabia and 40.8% for the UK).- Impact of the Informational Video during the study: The study indicated that the majority of participants in both countries became more interested in IoT after watching the video. - Future Smart Home Device Purchase: 86.2% of participants from Saudi Arabia planned to purchase a smart home device in the future, while only 57.1% of participants from the UK had similar plans.üìä Some key Insights from Inferential Statistics:- The chi-square test revealed that education level, privacy concerns, and the need for safety guarantees exhibited significant differences between participants from Saudi Arabia and the UK.- The Mann-Whitney U test indicated that knowledge about smart home devices showed no significant difference between the two countries."}, {'name': 'Sales Analysis for an E-commerce Store', 'description': "In today's dynamic business environment, staying ahead of the game requires more than just offering top-notch products or services. It calls for a deep understanding of your sales processes, and the ability to identify potential pitfalls before they become revenue roadblocks. For an online store manager, recognizing cities with underperforming sales can be an alarming trend, signaling a serious issue within the sales pipeline.üîç Identifying the GapsThe motivation for this project was rooted in a pressing business concern. The manager of the online store observed considerable losses in several cities, an anomaly that couldn't be attributed to chance. It was evident that the sales pipeline needed a thorough audit to uncover any gaps and resolve them proactively. This required a comprehensive overview of every variable in the sales process, coupled with an in-depth analysis of the sources of profit and loss.üí° The Solution: Sales Analysis DashboardTo tackle these issues head-on, we developed a Sales Analysis Dashboard ‚Äì a powerful tool designed to provide a user-friendly interface for sales tracking and a complete understanding of profit and loss sources.Here are some benefits of the Sales Analysis Dashboard:üí∞ Increased Profit Margins: By identifying and addressing the issues related to unregulated discounts, you can significantly boost profit margins.üìä Informed Decision-Making: With a clear overview of your sales data, you can make informed decisions to optimize your strategies and resources.üìà Spotting Trends: The dashboard's time series chart lets you spot trends and patterns that can guide your future business plans.üë• Geographical Insights: Identifying high and low-performing cities provides a strategic advantage in sales and marketing efforts.üîç Category Optimization: Understanding which categories are driving your sales and profits allows you to optimize your product offerings."}, {'name': 'Survey-Based Dashboard for Romantic Relationship Behaviors and Family Influence', 'description': 'In the realm of romantic relationships, understanding the dynamics between partners and the influence of family environments is a complex but profoundly important pursuit. Our "Behavioral Study of Romantic Relationships" dashboard was designed to serve as a comprehensive repository for the results of a survey-based research study. It not only simplifies the presentation of survey findings but also equips researchers with a powerful tool to explore and analyze data in-depth, aiding the creation of future research papers with ease.‚úÖ Survey Insights, All in One PlaceThe motivation behind creating this dashboard was to provide a centralized space for survey results, enabling researchers to effortlessly access and analyze data related to romantic relationship behaviors and the impact of family environments. With three distinct sections, it\'s a versatile tool for comprehensive research.‚úÖ Key Benefits of the Dashboard- Effortless Data Access: All survey results are presented in a user-friendly format, simplifying the presentation of findings and saving researchers valuable time.- Flexible Data Analysis: Researchers can effortlessly apply filters and select parameters to dynamically change the charts in the dashboard, thereby enabling a multitude of research avenues without the need for extensive data manipulation.- Deeper Insights: With the ability to compare variables like age, gender, and education, researchers can uncover nuanced relationships within the data.- Family Impact Assessment: Understanding the influence of family environments on romantic relationships is made easy with the side-by-side comparisons.- Resourceful for Future Research: Researchers can leverage the dashboard\'s flexibility to generate additional research papers or explore related topics, ensuring the study\'s data continues to provide valuable insights.Connect with me if you need to build a customized dashboard for your research.'}, {'name': 'Telecom Churn Analysis Dashboard', 'description': "The project aimed to help a Telecommunication company based in California to understand their customer base, and more importantly to understand and predict customer churn in order to develop some retention strategies.To fulfill all needs in one place, a web app was designed to help the business understand and tackle customer churn in a user-friendly way. The interactive app provides managers with the insights they need to retain valuable customers and grow their businesses.The app has two main tabs:üìä Tab 1: Data Understanding and Churn VisualizationIn the first tab, the aim was to understand the data and see how customers behave.üîç Find out who's leaving, staying, or joining. Filters can be used to see if certain campaigns, services, or customer groups are making a difference.üîç Explore different types of contracts to see how they affect customer churn. Are month-to-month, one-year, or two-year contracts making a difference?üîç Get to know customers better. Charts show things like how many are men or women, if they're married, their ages, and where most of them live. You can look closer by using filters.üîç See which services customers use, like phone service or internet. Filters can help to find out if the way they pay or the contract type affects their choices.üîç Find out which ads work best. projects: [{'name': 'Enterprise Network Design and Deployment Project.', 'description': "Description:I designed and implemented a robust enterprise network using the Cisco Hierarchical Model (Core, Distribution, Access). The network features VRRP, LACP, DHCP, DMZ, Fortinet Firewalls, VLANs, VTP, Wireless Controllers, IP Phones VoIP. Initially developed in Cisco Packet Tracer, then simulated in GNS3, and finally deployed in a real-world environment for high availability and security across multiple departments.Key Features:-Hierarchical Model: Optimized network structure for performance and scalability.-High Availability: Implemented VRRP and LACP for redundancy and load balancing.-Security: Configured Fortinet firewalls for perimeter protection.-VLAN Management: Created and managed VLANs using VTP.-Advanced Switching: Used RSTP and BPDU Guard for network stability.-Routing: Applied OSPF for efficient routing.-IP Management: Deployed Windows Server 2019 for DHCP services.-DMZ: Set up a DMZ for critical services.-VoIP: Integrated IP Phones for voice communication.-Multilayer Switching: Enabled inter-VLAN and SVI's routing with multilayer switches."}, {'name': 'Fast Typer Mini JAVA Game.', 'description': 'Description:A console-based typing challenge game to improve typing speed and accuracy, developed in Java. Utilizing various design patterns for efficient software design.Key Features:=>Design Patterns:-Singleton: Manages a single game configuration instance.-Factory: Creates different game objects for easy updates.-Strategy: Adapts scoring algorithms based on mode.-Decorator: Adds features like visual effects without altering core functionality.-User Interface: Console UI displays prompts, timers, and scores for enhanced engagement.-Typing Challenge: Players type words within a time limit, scoring based on speed and accuracy.-Game Modes: Includes timed challenges and practice options.'}, {'name': 'Linux Servers: (HTTP/Apache), DHCP, and DNS.', 'description': 'Description:This project involves creating and configuring various Linux servers, including HTTP (Apache), DHCP, and DNS, to effectively host multiple websites and manage network services.Key Features:-Case 1: Distinct Websites by IP: Configured two websites on the same Apache server, each with a unique IP address using Virtual Hosts.-Case 2: Distinct Websites by Port: Set up two websites differentiated by port numbers with DNS resolution.-DHCP Server: Implemented a DHCP server for dynamic IP address assignment, enhancing network management.-DNS Server: Established a DNS server for resolving domain names to IP addresses for easier website access.'}, {'name': 'School Departments and Students Monitoring Website.', 'description': 'Description:This mini-project develops a web app to manage student and department information using Java EE, Spring Data JPA, and MySQLdatabase for data storage and management. The application organizes student records, departmental details, with UML used for design.Key Features:-Student Management: CRUD functionality for student records.-Department & Course Management: Organizes academic structures.-Backend Development: Efficient CRUD operations with Java EE and Spring Data JPA.-Database Management: Scalable data handling with MySQL.-UML Design: Visualizes system architecture.-OOP Principles: Modular codebase for maintainability.'}, {'name': 'Secure Desktop Chat Application.', 'description': 'Description:I developed a secure desktop-based client-server chat application using Python and sockets, with a strong focus on ensuring the confidentiality, integrity, and traceability of communications. The application employs SHA-256 hashing to protect sensitive data, and uses key-based cryptography with digital signatures to verify message integrity. It also features a secure authentication mechanism, where user passwords are hashed and stored securely to prevent unauthorized access. Additionally, the server logs all signed messages along with sender and receiver details, and records every login attempt, both successful and failed, enabling complete traceability and providing accounting security for monitoring communication history and tracking authentication activities.Key Features:Client-Server Architecture: Client-server architecture for real-time communication.Secure Authentication: SHA-256 hashing for password storage and data protection.Confidentiality: Applied SHA-256 hashing to protect sensitive data transmitted across the network.Integrity Verification: Digital signatures for integrity verification.Traceability & Accounting Security: Logging of messages and authentication attempts for traceability.Real-time Communication: Enabled real-time messaging between clients and the server with efficient management of multiple connections.'}, {'name': 'Smart Farm Automation Project.', 'description': "Description:This project automates plant care using IoT technologies. The system automatically waters plants when moisture levels drop using the Blynk platform for real-time monitoring, this project was showcased at the Higher School of Technology (EST) in Fes.Key Features:-Automatic Irrigation: Activates watering based on soil moisture levels.-Environmental Monitoring: Tracks temperature and light for optimal growth.-IoT Integration: Utilizes ESP microcontrollers for efficient data management.-Blynk Platform: Allows remote control and real-time data access via mobile.-Presentation: Demonstrated the project's feasibility at EST Fes."}, {'name': 'VPN Links Creation using OpenVPN, L2TP, and PPTP in Linux.', 'description': 'Description:This project involves creating VPN links using OpenVPN, L2TP, and PPTP in a Linux environment to establish secure internet connections for remote users, ensuring data confidentiality and integrity.Key Features:-OpenVPN: Configured server and client connections for secure data tunneling.-L2TP/IPsec: Implemented L2TP over IPsec for enhanced security and authentication.-PPTP: Set up PPTP links for quick connections while evaluating security.-Linux Setup: Performed all configurations in a Linux environment, improving networking skills.'}]

projects:
[{'name': 'Optimisation du Probl√®me du Voyageur de Commerce (TSP)', 'description': 'Dans le cadre de notre formation en analytique de donn√©es, nous avons d√©velopp√© un projet visant √† r√©soudre le Probl√®me du Voyageur de Commerce (TSP), un probl√®me fondamental en optimisation combinatoire. L‚Äôobjectif √©tait de concevoir et comparer plusieurs algorithmes permettant de minimiser la distance totale parcourue en visitant un ensemble de points une seule fois avant de revenir au point de d√©part.

Nous avons impl√©ment√© plusieurs approches :

Plus Proche Voisin (Nearest Neighbor) : approche gloutonne choisissant syst√©matiquement le sommet le plus proche.
Insertion la Plus Proche (Nearest Insertion) : construction progressive du circuit en ins√©rant les sommets √† la position minimisant la distance.
Insertion la Plus Lointaine (Farthest Insertion) : ajout des sommets les plus √©loign√©s pour am√©liorer la qualit√© de la solution.
Force Brute (Brute Force) : exploration exhaustive de toutes les permutations pour obtenir la solution optimale.
Technologies et m√©thodologie :
Langage C pour l‚Äôimpl√©mentation des algorithmes et la gestion des structures de donn√©es.
Matrice d‚Äôadjacence pour mod√©liser les distances entre les sommets du graphe.
Comparaison des performances en fonction du temps d‚Äôex√©cution et de l‚Äôefficacit√© des solutions obtenues.
R√©sultats et analyse :
Les algorithmes heuristiques comme l‚Äôinsertion la plus proche et l‚Äôinsertion la plus lointaine offrent un bon compromis entre rapidit√© et pr√©cision. La force brute garantit la solution optimale mais devient impraticable pour de grandes instances en raison de sa complexit√© exponentielle.

Ce projet nous a permis d‚Äôapprofondir nos connaissances en th√©orie des graphes, structures de donn√©es et optimisation, tout en appliquant des concepts essentiels √† la r√©solution de probl√®mes r√©els.

Email communication is an essential part of both personal and professional life. To address this issue, Zakaria Ouhchouch and I developed a Machine Learning-based spam detection system capable of accurately classifying emails as spam or ham (non-spam).

Approach & Methodology:
We explored and implemented two widely used algorithms: Logistic Regression and Na√Øve Bayes. Our workflow involved:

Data Preprocessing:

Removing special characters and numbers

Tokenizing and vectorizing text using the Bag-of-Words model
Model Training & Evaluation:

Logistic Regression: Achieved 94.98% accuracy and an F1-score of 82%
Na√Øve Bayes: Achieved 93.5% accuracy and an F1-score of 80%
Addressed class imbalance (4825 ham vs. 747 spam emails) by applying class weights, improving spam recall to 84%

Data Visualization:
Generated word clouds to identify common words in spam (e.g., "free," "win," "prize") and ham emails (e.g., "meeting," "tomorrow," "thanks")
Key Takeaways
Logistic Regression provided a better balance between precision and recall
Na√Øve Bayes demonstrated efficiency in handling text classification
The importance of class balancing to improve spam detection rates
Gained practical insights into text preprocessing, feature extraction, and model evaluation

[{'name': 'Camera Calibration & Motion Analysis App', 'description': 'I collaborated with a team to develop a comprehensive desktop application for calibrating smartphone video footage and performing precise motion analysis. Our solution enables researchers to extract quantitative measurements from video sequences by implementing advanced computer vision techniques.

The application features a complete calibration pipeline using checkerboard patterns to correct optical distortions and calculate camera intrinsic/extrinsic parameters. We implemented homography matrix extraction to convert pixel coordinates to real-world measurements, allowing for accurate velocity and acceleration calculations of moving objects in video sequences. projects:
[{'name': 'Academix', 'description': 'The Ultimate, All-in-one ERP for Higher-Ed Institutions'}, {'name': 'Communizer', 'description': 'Popular software has always been appealing to adversaries, as related vulnerabilities are synonymous with millions of exposed businesses. Collaborative intrusion detection, as well as software self-protection try to alleviate this situation, but lack either autonomy and adaptation or Internet-scale oversight and mitigation.

Communizer is a collaborative cloud-based framework that creates communities of self-protecting software across organizations. It allows community members to turn their common weaknesses into collaborative and proactive self-protection, by empowering them to detect intrusions, exchange alerts and anticipate attacks. To this end, we extend the autonomic computing model, as implemented by our Immunizer framework, by integrating multiple MAPE-K control loops through cloud-based coordination. We adopt a hierarchical, clustered, parallelized and asynchronous microservice architecture. This unique combination strives to optimize scalability, maintainability and resilience, without compromising privacy or accuracy.

We also designed a trust-based multi-level alert coordination system, as well as a lightweight alert coordination message exchange format. In particular, our coordination system addresses insider attacks by detecting and blacklisting untrustworthy members. It also identifies and neutralizes selfish members through a specifically designed probabilistic model.

The analysis, optimization and evaluation of our framework show a drastic reduction of the monitoring load on community members, while ensuring a high attack detection rate, even for small-scope attacks.'}]

about:
In the late 1980s and early 1990s bridge router wars raged. Responding to the debate, I created a hybrid bridge-router architecture 

1. that provided the first example of software-configurable network switching device virtualization and 

2. that later became pervasive throughout the Internet and private Intranets.

While cloud computing probably starts in the 1980s thanks to the efforts of groups like Project Athena, where I worked for a time, the network device virtualization concepts that I pioneered tremendously facilitate the modern form of cloud computation.

The Clearpoint Constellation Series of bridge routers instantiated my hybrid bridge-router design.

PC Magazine reviewed the Constellation Pyxis/Pixis Bridge Router and awarded it Editor's Choice status in March, 1993.

More recently I developed a Java-based multimode High Frequency, Medium Frequency, Day Trading application with a new approach to risk management, trading strategies, and trading portfolio optimizations as well as with a scalable innovative distributed architecture. It simulates the Meta-Trader IV Expert Adviser capability via a built in Python interpreter. In simulation it beats top hedge fund software. At some point I may add a Common Lisp interpreter in order to take advantage of some Lisp-based expert system trading software.

The jobs below represent a subset of development  and consulting work in which I have taken part and that are relevant to my employment goal.

Because my experience is wide-ranging and varied and for the sake of clarity, I have a legal version as well as an engineering version of my resume. After the USPTO registration license and the image of the PC Magazine Editor's Choice Award, I provide each version of the resume. I put the abridged versions of the resume first, and the more complete versions of the resume then follow.

Languages used : React ( Javascript Library ) , Javascript , Tailwind Css , The movie db api .'}, {'name': "let's Marry", 'description': "let's Marry is a web application to facilitate the process of booking wedding venues using LARAVEL ( PHP FRAMEWORK ) .
it's a web application where client can book wedding venues and view his reservations .
‚Ä¢ owner can post venues , edit on his venues , Delete his venues , and view his venues .
‚Ä¢ admin can ban clients , can ban owners and if he ban an owner his venues won't appear in venues page , he can also disable venues .

‚Ä¢ At the level of database relationships client can reserve many venues and venue can be reserved by many clients so it's clear that it's many to many relationship .
‚Ä¢ in the other side owner can post many venues and venue can belong to only one owner so the relationship is one to many .

‚Ä¢ in let's marry there are four interfaces :
‚Ä¢ guest interface where the guest can browse freely in home page and venues page .
‚Ä¢ client interface where the client has an additional page where he can find all the informations about his reservations .
‚Ä¢ owner interface where the owner will find my venues page where the owner can add new venues , edit on his venues and delete his venues .
‚Ä¢ admin dashboard : in the admin interface the admin will find the stats page where he can take a look at all the stats , there is also a venues page where the admin can activate a pending venue and disable an active venue , an owners page where he can ban owners or activate banned owners , and a clients page where he can ban clients or activate banned clients .

‚Ä¢ for technologies in the backEnd I used laravel , sql , and Eloquent ( Eloquent is an object relational mapper ) , in the frontEnd I used HTML , Tailwind Css , and Alpine js .

‚Ä¢ I learned from this project how to really use Laravel , how to handle big projects , how to build a database and deal with it ."}]

[{'name': 'Machine Learning and NLP-based approach for  constraint acquisition problems', 'description': '*Abstract*
Constraint Programming (CP) is widely used platform in industry and research for modeling and solving complex constraint satisfaction and optimization problems.
Nonetheless, the automated model reformulation platforms that aims to assist the users in modeling and solving constraint problems remains restricted. This level of restriction is caused by the mathematical modeling and programming skills required to handle many types and forms of NP-complete decision problems, such as planning, scheduling, and resource optimization challenges. In this context, we present our research, which aims to integrate Natural Language Processing (NLP) with constraint acquisition via a conversational agent in order to make the constraint programming paradigm more accessible to a wider variety of users. The purpose of this study is to develop an intelligent constraint acquisition system that allows a novice user to communicate a problem in natural language to the system that will describes the given problem as a constraint network, solves it, and presents alternate solutions to the user if any available.

*Keywords*
Constraint Acquisition Problem, Constraint Programming, Natural Language Processing,
Deep Learning.'}, {'name': 'Conception et r√©alisation d‚Äôune plateforme  de freelance avec le Framework Laravel', 'description': "Le but principal de notre travail est l'√©tude, la conception et la r√©alisation d'une plateforme de freelance, qui permet aux clients de recruter des Freelancers et aux Freelancers de postuler √† des projets. projects:
[{'name': 'Movie Recommender & Sentiment Analysis System', 'description': 'This project combines recommender systems and sentiment analysis to enhance the movie search and discovery experience.

The pipeline starts with data collection, where datasets of movie reviews are used to train both machine learning models and deep learning models (RNN) for sentiment classification. At the same time, movie metadata is collected to build an item-based recommendation system.

After data preprocessing, the models are trained and evaluated to ensure robust performance. The system integrates two main components:

Sentiment Analysis Module: Analyzes real-time scraped movie reviews and classifies them as positive or negative.

Recommender System Module: Suggests similar movies based on item-based collaborative filtering.

Finally, the project was deployed using Flask as a web platform, providing users with an interactive interface. A user can search for a movie, and the system will:

Scrape real-time movie information and reviews.

Perform sentiment analysis on the reviews.

Display movie details along with recommended similar movies.

This project demonstrates the integration of Natural Language Processing (NLP), Deep Learning (RNN), Recommender Systems, and Web Development with Flask into a complete end-to-end solution.'}, {'name': 'Blood Group Detection Using Deep Learning', 'description': 'The main goal of this project is to develop an innovative system for detecting human blood groups using deep learning techniques. Traditional serological blood typing, while reliable, can be time-consuming, resource-intensive, and sometimes inaccessible in urgent or remote contexts.

This project explores two approaches:

Blood Image-Based Detection:

Uses images of blood samples to identify specific antigen reactions (A, B, D/Rh).

Leverages computer vision and deep learning to automate classification into blood groups (O-, O+, A-, A+, B-, B+, AB-, AB+).

Offers fast, automated, and non-invasive detection suitable for emergencies and field applications.

Fingerprint-Based Detection:

Explores the potential correlation between fingerprint patterns and blood groups.

Provides a fully non-invasive method if the correlation is validated, potentially applicable in medical, security, or forensic contexts.

Objectives:

Study the feasibility of both approaches and combine them to enhance accuracy and robustness.

Use a comprehensive dataset of blood images and fingerprints linked with blood group information.

Apply image processing, machine learning, and statistical analysis to develop predictive models.

Provide an accessible and innovative solution for blood group detection, suitable for medical emergencies, biometric security, and forensic investigations.'}]

I thrive at the intersection of AI, machine learning, and robotics, and I love building systems that integrate advanced computer vision techniques, like the MosaicBot I designed, which automates the sorting of mosaic pieces using OpenCV and Raspberry Pi. projects:
[{'name': 'FocusFriend', 'description': "This project leverages the Pepper robot and Choregraphe software to create an interactive and engaging tool for early ADHD diagnosis in children. By using games and a specially designed diagnostic dialogue, the robot helps reduce anxiety and facilitates more accurate self-reporting from kids. The goal is to improve early detection and support for ADHD, combining robotics with healthcare to enhance children's well-being and reduce stigma."}, {'name': 'MosaicBot', 'description': "Project Overview
MosaicBot is an innovative solution designed to sort Fassi mosaic pieces by color and shape. Using a Lynxmotion LA5D robotic arm, OpenCV for computer vision, and a Raspberry Pi 3, the system aims to repurpose small mosaic pieces that are often wasted in the old medina of Fes.

Inspiration
As students at UEMF in Fes and being a Fassi, I noticed that mosaic artisans in the old medina often have small, mixed pieces of mosaic that go to waste. We envisioned MosaicBot to sort these pieces automatically for use in other decorative objects.

Development Process

Concept and Research:
Visited the old medina and collected unused mosaic pieces from artisans.
Planned the project to create an automated sorting system.

Programming and Testing:
Programmed the Lynxmotion LA5D robotic arm using Python.
Implemented OpenCV algorithms on the Raspberry Pi 3 for color and shape recognition.

Assembly and Integration:
Assembled the robotic arm and integrated it with the Raspberry Pi 3.
Ensured smooth communication between the vision system and the robotic arm.

Testing and Refinement:
Conducted extensive testing to refine accuracy and movements.
Optimized the sorting process for various sizes and shapes of mosaic pieces.

Final Presentation:
Achieved a functional system that successfully sorted mosaic pieces.
Presented the final result to our teacher, demonstrating the project's capabilities.

Conclusion
MosaicBot reduces waste and enhances the usability of mosaic pieces in Fes. This project provided valuable technical experience and demonstrated the practical impact of combining robotics and computer vision. We look forward to exploring further applications."}]

projects:
[{'name': 'AI-Powered Question Answering with LangChain and Google Gemini', 'description': 'This project demonstrates a Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) pipeline for answering questions based on a set of documents. It uses Google Gemini as the large language model (LLM) and FAISS for efficient document retrieval. The pipeline involves loading documents, creating embeddings using HuggingFaceEmbeddings, storing them in a FAISS vector store, and leveraging LangChain tools to build the RAG chain. The system enables answering complex questions by combining the knowledge from the retrieved documents with the language capabilities of Google Gemini, providing accurate and insightful responses. The project includes handling input and output, allowing users to ask questions and receive answers with references to relevant source documents.

Key Technologies:
Python, Google Gemini, FAISS, LangChain, HuggingFace Embeddings'}, {'name': 'Image Captioning using TensorFlow', 'description': "This project involves developing an image caption generation model using deep learning techniques. The model utilizes pre-trained InceptionV3 or DenseNet201 models for feature extraction from input images. The features are then combined with word embeddings of the caption text and fed into an LSTM or GRU network to generate descriptive captions.

Key Features:
* Feature Extraction: Extracts relevant image features using InceptionV3 or DenseNet201.
* Preprocessing and Tokenization: Cleans and tokenizes image captions for input to the model.
* Data Preparation: Prepares data for training the model using efficient techniques like numpy's memmap.
* Model Training: Trains the LSTM or GRU model to generate descriptive image captions.
* Sequence Generation: Generates predicted caption sequences.
* Data Generator: Uses a custom data generator to load data efficiently during training.

Technical Details:
* Languages: Python
* Libraries: TensorFlow, Keras, NumPy, Pandas, Matplotlib, scikit-learn
* Model Architecture: LSTM or GRU-based recurrent neural network

Skills Demonstrated:
Deep learning, Natural language processing (NLP), Image processing, Data preprocessing and manipulation, Python, Model training and evaluation, Working with large datasets"}]

I am a mission-driven leader at the intersection of mental healthcare advocacy, product innovation, and software engineering.

Before my shift into technology, I encountered the complexities of mental health challenges firsthand‚Äì navigating severe depression, stigma, and the challenge of finding the right care for my needs‚Äì but through that journey, I found purpose, committing myself to advocating for the improvement of mental health services.

This commitment led me to a rewarding career in mental health and suicide prevention, where I‚Äôve been interviewed for prestigious news media and feature-length documentaries, testified before Congress, took the stage at the Grammys, and summited mountains for suicide prevention fundraisers. Seeking to amplify my impact, I transitioned into software engineering and product development, where I now focus on building innovative, evidence-based solutions that expand access to quality mental healthcare.

I thrive at the intersection of mission, vision, and execution. By bridging my lived experience, advocacy, and technical expertise, I aim to build the next generation of transformative mental health solutions, driving meaningful change at scale.

In Dungeon Adventure, the main goal is to collect as many treasures as possible, avoid cunning enemies, and ultimately confront the boss at the end of the dungeon. The game features dynamic maps, challenging enemies, and exciting collectibles such as coins, health potions, and mystery boxes..

about:
I‚Äôm a Web Developer with a background in teaching Mathematics. Growing up in a small country like Nepal, where education for girls is never considered, I was fortunate to have a chance to pursue academics and learn basic computer knowledge during high school.

I was excited, curious, and fascinated by everything I was learning. It was another world for me. I felt like I obtained the power to see other parts of the world, and I could connect with people globally. That's when I decided I want to learn more, but as stated earlier, it wasn‚Äôt easy for girls to step out and do what they wanted.

After facing many obstacles, I took a Graphic Design course and started working as a Graphic Designer while also learning how to code with my friend. I chose different career paths, where I learned the fine art of customer service and teaching maths. But deep down, I always wanted to be in the technology field. I never gave up, which is why even after so many years, I joined Flatiron School - a coding Bootcamp - to fulfill my dream.

No matter where I work, I always bring the same level of dedication, hard work, passion, and strong work ethic I have always had. As a multilingual person, I easily adapt to different environments and cultures. I am a big believer in continuous improvement, so I am always ready and willing to take on new challenges.

Besides coding I love to cook, dance, read books, and learn about new technologies.

about:
I'm an NLP Research Associate at MBZUAI(and a Research Fellow at Riken), my current research focuses on representational analysis to understand how the reasoning mechanism and knowledge are encoded in the parameters and activations of large language models (LLMs). This research seeks to uncover the mechanisms through which LLMs store, retrieve, and process information (reasoning), offering insights into the inner workings of these advanced AI systems. 

Before this, I extensively worked on Arabic natural language processing and machine learning, contributing to developing generative LLMs, benchmarks for Arabic natural language generation, and evaluating machine translation systems for various Arabic dialects. My work aims to advance the understanding and capabilities of NLP technologies and a better understanding of LLMs.

Additionally, I am interested in generative AI, multilingualism, multi-modality, and low-resource languages, aiming to enhance the capabilities and accessibility of NLP technologies across diverse linguistic contexts.
headline: NLP Researcher @MBZUAI | Research Fellow @Riken AIP | ex Walmart | Generative AI | Interpretability

about:
I‚Äôm an AI product leader turned medtech operator, passionate about building meaningful technology at the intersection of healthcare, data, and intelligent systems. My journey began in data science, where I developed a foundation in analytics consulting and applied machine learning. Over time, I transitioned into AI product management, leading enterprise SaaS and legal tech solutions that translated complex models into human-centered products.

Today, I‚Äôve carried that experience into digital health and neuromodulation. I serve as Operating Partner at Innostim MedTech, leading strategy, operations, and commercialization in Asia, where our direct-to-consumer model makes advanced therapies accessible to patients at scale. In parallel, I act as Chief Data Officer at Australis Scientific, our Harvard-incubated partner in North America, where the model is reimbursement-driven, embedding wearables into the clinical care pathway for urologists and payors.

This fusion of two complementary approaches ‚Äî DTC in Asia and reimbursed MedTech-as-a-Service in North America ‚Äî positions our work as a blueprint for how next-generation medtech startups can globalize while staying patient-centric.

Across each chapter, I‚Äôve remained committed to bridging clinical insight, algorithmic intelligence, and product strategy ‚Äî and to designing systems that empower experts, simplify complexity, and serve real human needs. Today, that means helping set the standard for a new class of medtech startups: cross-border, customer-focused, and globally scalable.

about:
As a 10-time CTO in enterprise search, I‚Äôve watched the same cycle repeat for decades: enterprises have been told that centralizing their data will finally deliver the elusive ‚Äúsingle source of truth.‚Äù

But mergers, SaaS sprawl, and cloud migrations have made this dream impossible.

Now, with AI, we‚Äôre at it again ‚Äì trying to force ever-growing, messy datasets into static vector databases.

It‚Äôs time for a new paradigm.

That‚Äôs why I founded SWIRL - the intelligent orchestration layer for enterprise data in the AI age.

SWIRL lets data stay exactly where it lives, seamlessly connecting across over 100 enterprise platforms. 

It dynamically searches, intelligently re-ranks, and securely delivers exactly the right data to your AI, exactly when you need it.

- No painful and costly migrations.
- No redundant silos and database bills.
- No unnecessary chaos.

Just instant, secure, actionable intelligence.

Centralization had its chance. Intelligent orchestration is the future. 

Let SWIRL take you there.

Mounssif Bouhlaoui is a Lead Software Engineer and Community Architect dedicated to empowering individuals and communities through technology, engaging events, and mindset mastery. His career spans from industrial automation to full-stack development, driven by a passion for connecting people and unlocking their potential. As a graduate of ALX SE and an alumnus of All In Africa, Mounssif expertly merges his technical acumen with dynamic community leadership.

He's not just building applications; he's architecting ecosystems of growth and inspiration. Previously, Mounssif partnered with Sophie Barbier to create PrepForSuccess.ai, an AI-powered platform for interview preparation, where he served as the technical driving force. He also hosts numerous events, Fireside Chats, Podcasts and workshops like "Empowered Imposter Syndrome," helping individuals transform self-doubt into a source of strength. A large array of my experience revolves around Tree-based models in Supervised learning(Gradient Boosting, Random Forests and Decision Trees) and Clustering in Unsupervised Learning(kmeans, Hierarchical clustering, Spectral clustering). My Python experience has primarily been for Deep Learning(keras and PyTorch) and Matrix methods and operations. I have also developed a strong interest in manual Python implementations of machine learning algorithms(NumPy, SciPy) such as Support Vector Machines, Artificial Neural Networks, kmeans, Hierarchical clustering etc in Python to understand and use them better.

A large part of my data science experience lies in Healthcare, followed by social data, real estate and communications. However, I am very excited for novel learning opportunities across fields where I can use mathematical, technological, creative and leadership skills in tandem to solve real world problems. I live my life on a quote - ‚ÄúThe biggest quality you need as a data scientist is the willingness to feel stupid every single day.‚Äù

 Feel free to reach out to chat about anything above, anything that could be above or just as a friendly greeting!
projects: [{'name': 'Predicting GPS location from Wi-Fi data', 'description': "The project aimed to look at the Wi-Fi data collected from smartphones(Wi-Fi ID, signal strength, accuracy etc.) and use those as predictors to predict the GPS location of an individual. In the realm of digital phenotyping, data from smartphones can be used to predict a person's mental state in advance, to enable faster response systems to anxiety attacks, depression etc. However, since grabbing the GPS data is more challenging than other kinds of data, it is usually the case that there are far less data points for GPS coordinates compared to the other kinds of data. Therefore, we created a basic model using artificial neural networks, that took in WI-Fi data and churned out GPS coordinates. The project was put on hold after initial modelling as we await more data."}, {'name': "Predicting ICD-9 codes from doctor's discharge notes", 'description': "The project took in doctor's discharge notes in text form and tried to predict the ICD-9 diagnosis codes from them. Word embeddings were created using the novel Fasttext model and the modelling was done using a Recurrent Neural Network architecture, primarily composed of GRU units. The top 5 ICD-9 codes and their text documents were chosen due to time and resource constraints, but it could be extended without much additional effort."}]

projects:
[{'name': 'NBA Player Performance Analysis: PCA, Hierarchical Clustering, and K-Means Clustering', 'description': 'This project delves into the realm of data science and sports analytics by harnessing machine learning and data mining techniques for basketball performance analysis in the National Basketball Association (NBA). The primary objectives are to employ Principal Component Analysis (PCA) and Clustering methods to gain insights into advanced measures of basketball performance. PCA identifies the most influential variables, while Clustering classifies similar observations using unsupervised classification algorithms. By analyzing NBA player data, this project aims to assess player performance comprehensively, extending beyond mere point statistics, and provide valuable insights to aid coaches in decision-making. The results will be visually presented through graphs and tables, highlighting the impact of clusters on the data.

Problematic:

The study addresses several pivotal questions, including:

1) Identifying the best NBA players in history based on a wide range of basketball skills rather than just points.

2) Evaluating whether NBA players possess skills that surpass their designated positions and how this information can assist coaches in making informed decisions about player selection and evaluation.'}, {'name': 'Exchange rate time series forecasting using an MLP neural network', 'description': "This project delves into exchange rate forecasting for the EUR/USD currency pair, utilizing Multi-Layer Perceptron (MLP) neural networks. Time series analysis is the foundation of this study, aiming to predict future exchange rate movements, particularly in volatile financial markets.

Context:

Time series analysis is an essential discipline with diverse applications across various fields, including business, economics, finance, and computer science. The project addresses the intricacies of exchange rate forecasting, a critical endeavour for businesses and financial institutions. Exchange rates often exhibit nonlinearity, chaos, noise, and non-stationarity, making traditional forecasting methods like ARIMA less effective.

Objective:

The project employs MLP neural networks to overcome these challenges as a viable alternative for estimating exchange rates. Specifically, it focuses on predicting the EUR/USD exchange rate's future movements. The dataset spans from February 2015 to September 2016, comprising 400 daily observations. The first 300 observations serve as training data, while the remaining 100 are designated for testing the model's predictive accuracy.

In essence, this project endeavours to harness the capabilities of MLP neural networks to enhance the accuracy and reliability of exchange rate forecasts, addressing the complexities inherent in financial time series data."}]

projects:
[{'name': 'HR Analytics Dashboard with Power BI and Machine Learning', 'description': 'In this project, I designed a professional and interactive HR dashboard using Power BI, focused on employee satisfaction and attrition analysis. The dashboard enables Human Resources teams to monitor key workforce metrics and anticipate employee departures.

Main features:

Analysis of employee attrition and satisfaction

Visualization of key HR KPIs (headcount, attrition rate, average salary...)

Predictive analytics using a Random Forest model trained in Google Colab

Data structured in a star schema for optimized analysis

Multi-page Power BI report: Overview, Employee Data, Satisfaction Analysis, Attrition Focus, and ML Results'}, {'name': 'MediPortal', 'description': "Project Overview
This project aims to develop a management system for a medical practice, designed to centralize and automate key processes such as patient management, consultations, appointments, medical records, and medical resources. The goal is to improve organizational efficiency and the quality of services provided by the practice, while ensuring compliance with medical data confidentiality standards.

Working Assumptions

Doctors and medical staff require a centralized system to manage patient records and consultations.

Automating appointments and reminders helps reduce errors and missed appointments.

Managing medical resources (schedules and assignments) enables better planning and utilization of resources.

Adopted Method
The system was modeled using UML to represent use cases and relationships between entities. The main features were defined to meet the needs of the different actors (doctors, secretaries, administrators, and patients). The design includes modules for secure authentication, consultation management, and the creation of medical records only when necessary (based on the doctor's diagnosis).

Results
The system enables:

Recording, viewing, and managing patients‚Äô medical records.

Scheduling and tracking medical appointments.

Managing consultations, prescriptions, and medical certificates.

Conclusions and Implications
The project meets the functional needs of a medical practice by offering a complete and intuitive solution. Future perspectives include integrating advanced features such as medical data analysis, teleconsultation, and compatibility with external medical platforms."}]

projects:
[{'name': 'Blockchain-based Federated Learning for Securing IoT devices.', 'description': 'Theme: Blockchain-based Federated Learning for Securing IoT devices.

- Technologies used:
   Federated learning, Blockchain, CNN, Deep Adversarial Learning, IPFS.

- Summary
The project has successfully demonstrated the integration of BC and FL, showcasing its potential to enhance the security, privacy, and collaborative nature of machine learning models. Throughout the project, we have explored various aspects of these two domains and developed a comprehensive system that combines their strengths.
By leveraging BC technology, we have established a decentralized and transparent framework for securely managing and validating transactions within the FL process. The immutability and consensus mechanisms provided by the BC ensure data integrity, accountability, and trust among the participating clients.
FL has enabled the collaborative training of machine learning models across multiple clients without compromising data privacy. By training models locally on client devices and sharing only encrypted model updates, we have preserved the privacy of sensitive data while benefiting from the collective intelligence of a distributed network.
The developed system incorporates a user-friendly website that serves as an interactive platform for users to engage with the integrated BC-FL system. Through the website, users can access valuable insights, monitor training progress, explore model performance, and interact with various visualizations and metrics.'}, {'name': 'Development of a monitoring tool', 'description': "End of studies' project
theme: Development of a monitoring tool.
The goal of this project was to create a monitoring solution to gather management information related to the use and performance of machines in a network while ensuring security and implementing an authentication system.
In a monitored network, it is often difficult to verify if management information has been altered before reaching the network administrator. Our solution ensures that when data is received, we can verify its legitimacy and detect any alterations or disruptions.
Project Components:
o Managed node: A monitored device in the network running an agent program (daemon). This component is also known as a node.
o Network management node: A device in the network responsible for collecting management information from managed nodes, acting as the network administrator, running a master node program (daemon). This component is also called the master node.
o Client: A user program that can collect management information from all managed nodes through one or more network management nodes."}]

projects:
[{'name': 'Simulation of a mobile robot through ROS2', 'description': 'ROS2 feels intimidating compared to ROS1. Now that ROS Noetic is reaching its end of life on May 29th, it‚Äôs time to step out of my comfort zone. That means updating my Ubuntu version and embracing the new features offered by ROS2.
This youtube video is what introduced me to the implementation of ROS2 : https://youtu.be/gISSSbYUZag?si=NG4kYFRp31WHYen2
To start this transition, I worked on a simulation of a mobile robot with the goal of detecting yellow tennis balls, tracking their position, and navigating toward them.Here are the steps I followed:
‚Ä¢	URDF Creation : Designed the robot in SOLIDWORKS and generated a URDF file, including sensors like LiDAR for mapping.
‚Ä¢	Simulation in Gazebo : Used the URDF to visualize and simulate the robot in a virtual environment where navigation is performed.
‚Ä¢	Object Detection by Color :  Implemented basic color-based vision to detect yellow tennis balls in the environment. 
This is just the beginning of the journey into ROS2.'}, {'name': 'ESP32-CAM Based RC Car ‚Äì Wireless Control via Web Server', 'description': "In this project, we developed a system to wirelessly control the trajectory of an RC car using the ESP32-CAM module, connected through a local web server over Wi-Fi. The ESP32-CAM combines a microcontroller with built-in Wi-Fi, Bluetooth, and a camera which makes it ideal for real-time video streaming and remote control.

By hosting a web server directly on the ESP32-CAM, we enabled users to view live camera feeds and control the car's movement through a browser, without the need for external hardware or internet access. This makes it a powerful demonstration of low-cost, edge-based IoT solutions in action.

 The project suggests :

- IoT Integration : Real-time wireless data exchange and control

- Cyber-Physical Systems : Integration of embedded hardware and networked software

- Remote Monitoring & Control : Enables seamless off-site interaction

This project serves as a practical, hands-on gateway to implementing core Industry 4.0 technologies across various sectors such as smart manufacturing, logistics, agriculture, home automation, and sustainable mobility systems."}]

projects:
[{'name': 'JIRA Statistics', 'description': "The aim of this project was to improve an already existing program which displays some of the company's statistics on television screens. This is mostly done by a multi-threaded program which fetches data provided by APIs and then generates simple HTML files. Those are further styled by another program.

The service I added to this program reads information from JIRA's REST API every ten minutes and compares it with data stored in a SQL database in order to provide statistics for the current number of issues per team as well as an indacation of how those numbers evolved in comparison with the previous week.

This database, which I also conceived, is fed by a program which stores data from the same API evry night. The necessity for this database arose from the fact that JIRA's REST API does not seem to support any form of history. This meant that I had to create my own history if I wanted to provide statistics regarding the evolution of issues."}, {'name': 'Visual Studio Extension', 'description': 'My first task as in intern at Croesus Finansoft was to extend an existing project and add a new feature to it. What had already been done was a wizard that used reflection to obtain all the desired public properties in an object contained in a .dll file and to generate a new class from them.

From this, I had to design a new wizard which can generate a data grid template by laying down code based on properties found in a .dll.'}]

Design and implement a compact and efficient infrastructure using Docker and Docker Compose within a virtual machine. Each service runs in a dedicated container, built from custom Dockerfiles using either the penultimate stable version of Alpine or Debian. projects:
[{'name': 'Inception', 'description': 'The "Inception" project is a system administration exercise aimed at enhancing Docker and container orchestration skills. The objective was to create a secure and scalable infrastructure for hosting a WordPress site with NGINX and MariaDB, all within Docker containers.

Key Features:
- Virtualization: Deployed a personal virtual machine to host Docker containers.
- Docker Configuration: Developed custom Dockerfiles for NGINX, WordPress, and MariaDB, ensuring each service runs in dedicated containers using Alpine or Debian.
- Service Orchestration: Used Docker Compose to manage and orchestrate services, with automatic restarts on crashes.
- Security: Configured NGINX with TLSv1.2/TLSv1.3 for HTTPS. Managed environment variables securely with a .env file.
- Persistent Storage: Implemented Docker volumes for WordPress files and database data.
- Networking: Established a Docker network for secure container communication.
- Domain Setup: Configured a custom domain (login.42.fr) pointing to the local IP for secure access.
- Automation: Created a Makefile to automate building and deploying Docker images with docker-compose.yml.
- User Management: Ensured secure WordPress user management with non-standard admin usernames.

Bonus Features:
- Added Redis caching for improved WordPress performance.

Technologies Used:
- Docker, Docker Compose
- NGINX, WordPress, MariaDB
- Alpine Linux, Debian
- TLSv1.2, TLSv1.3

The platform is directly connected to a network of certified p√©dopsychiatres, who monitor flagged cases through a secure dashboard. OndeChild‚Äôs AI evaluates the emotional content of each conversation, assigns a crisis severity level, and automatically routes critical or concerning cases to the appropriate specialist based on their expertise and availability.

OndeChild ensures children receive fast, discreet support ‚Äî whether through chatbot-guided coping resources or by escalating urgent cases for immediate professional care.

AI/NLP: Python with Hugging Face Transformers for sentiment, emotion, and intent detection

projects:
[{'name': "Master's Thesis: Analyzing and Modeling Turbulent Flows in an air-filled Square Cavity.", 'description': 'Project: Analyzing and Modeling Turbulent Flows in an air-filled Square Cavity. 

Objective: To Simulate Turbulent Flows inside a Vertical Square Cavity using the Eddy Viscosity Models and eventually evaluate their performance. 

In this investigation, a two-dimensional turbulent natural convection in an air-filled vertical square cavity was conducted. The cavity was 0.75 m high √ó 0.75 m wide, giving a 2D flow. The hot and cold walls of the cavity were isothermal at 50¬∞C and 10¬∞C, respectively, resulting in a Rayleigh number of 1.58 √ó 10^9. Several numerical simulations were performed using the following turbulence models: the Standard k-epsilon model, the RNG k-epsilon model, the Realizable k-epsilon model, and the Standard k-omega model. The simulations calculated the average temperature, average and fluctuating components of velocity, turbulent kinetic energy, and local Nusselt number. The results were presented and compared to the experimental benchmark data by Ampofo and karayiannis. A statistical analysis was conducted to evaluate the performance of the turbulence models in different flow fields.

Achievements: This Master Thesis was recognized and ranked first.'}, {'name': 'Soft Skills Project: Photovoltaic and Energy Efficiency at Mohamed V Foundation.', 'description': "Project: Study and Sizing of a Photovoltaic Field in collaboration with Mohamed V Foundation. 

Objective: To accurately size a photovoltaic field within the constraints of available space, aiming to optimize Energy Efficiency. 

The main challenge of this project was fitting an efficient photovoltaic system within the Foundation space. Ensuring cost-effectiveness while meeting these spatial constraints required precise planning and analysis.

In this context, my primary role was twofold. First, I led the financial analysis, evaluating potential costs against anticipated returns, ensuring the project's feasibility and sustainability. Subsequently, I tackled the responsibility of selecting the optimal components for the photovoltaic field. This entailed evaluating various available options, weighing their performance against cost, and ensuring that our chosen components would deliver the desired efficiency within the set budget.

Achievements: Through rigorous financial examination and judicious component selection, we successfully outlined a plan for a photovoltaic field that fit within the foundation's spatial and financial constraints. Our design was endorsed by the Mohamed V Foundation as both sustainable and cost-effective. It was also the top rated and first ranked among all the other Soft Skills Projects of the other graduate students."}]
